<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-14T23:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-14T23:34:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6767: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-15T13:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">April 15,
                                            1920—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:25
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>All the Czechs and other Allied forces to be evacuated are now
                                Manchuria Station and east of there. With no serious interruption we
                                hope to get them all Vladivostok in 30 days if the ships are there
                                to take them. There will be about 110 members of Service Corps to be
                                sent home. What arrangements have been made or will be made for
                                their transportation as it is understood the army has all gone?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>